==Old English==

===Etymology===
From Germanic: cognate with Old Frisian [[thenka]], Old High German [[thenken]] (German, Dutch [[denken]]), Old Saxon [[thenkian]], Old Norse [[þekkja]] (Old Swedish [[þækkia]]), Gothic [[𐌸𐌰𐌲𐌺𐌾𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'θenʧan/

===Verb===
'''þenċan''' (weak verb class 1: '''þenceþ'''/'''þencþ''' ‘he thinks’; '''þōhte''' ‘he thought’; '''ġeþōht''' past participle)
# to [[think]]

